Passio of Mauricius, Exuperius and Candidus

description: CCCC MS 361 is a manuscript of Gregory the Great's Pastoral Care from the branch of the textual tradition which is closest to that used in King Alfred the Great's translation. It was written in the eleventh century, probably not in England, but has later provenance at Malmesbury Abbey in Wiltshire. It contains corrections in the hand of William of Malmesbury (d. c. 1142).
